parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the VSC/ABS/Trac control system can cause the vehicle to become unstable, lose power, and experience sudden braking, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The VSC
ABS
and Trac control lights illuminate
the vehicle loses power
and the brakes may engage suddenly or fail to engage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes fail to engage properly
or the vehicle experiences sudden braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Frame corrosion can weaken the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The frame of the vehicle is corroded
and the vehicle may experience rust or structural damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight relay can cause the headlights to malfunction, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The headlights fail to turn on or turn off suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: VSC (Vehicle Stability Control) and TRAC (Traction Control) System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the VSC and TRAC system can cause the vehicle to lose control, resulting in accidents or near-misses, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The VSC and TRAC lights on the dashboard illuminate
accompanied by a beeping alarm
grinding noise
and sudden loss of power or braking ability. The vehicle may jerk or pull to one side
making it difficult to steer or control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the yaw rate sensor can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Grinding noise
loss of power steering
VSC and TRAC lights flashing
beeping sound
and sudden pulling to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Frame rust and corrosion can lead to structural failure, causing loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: Frame rust
corrosion
and holes in the frame
causing the vehicle to be unsafe to drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the concentric slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ESC system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: VSC and TRAC lights flashing
beeping sound
loss of power steering
sudden pulling to one side
and grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Electronic Stability Control (ESC) system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The VSC TRAC and TRAC OFF lights illuminate
accompanied by a beeping sound
grinding noise
and loss of power. The vehicle may jerk or pull to one side
making it difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and rust of the frame can lead to structural failure, compromising the safety of the vehicle and its occupants.
symptoms: Holes in the frame
excessive rust
soft or spongy frame
abnormal noises
and difficulty opening hood and tailgate latches.
